# Gitflow Workflow Commands

## 1. Initialize Git Repository
```sh
git init
git remote add origin <remote-repository-url>
```
## 2. Main and Develop Branches

Create and Push Main Branch
```sh
git checkout -b main
git push -u origin main
```
# Create and Push Develop Branch from Main
```sh
git checkout -b develop 
git push -u origin develop
```

## 3. Feature Branch

## Create Feature Branch from Develop
```sh
git checkout -b feature/<feature-name> develop
```

## 4. Feature Branch

Work on Feature and Commit Changes
```sh
git add .
git commit -m "Add new feature <feature-name>"
```

Push Feature Branch to Remote
```sh
git push -u origin feature/<feature-name>
```

## 5. Merge Feature Branch back into Develop after Completion

Push Feature Branch to Remote
```sh
git checkout develop
git merge feature/<feature-name>
```
Push Develop Branch with Merged Changes
```sh
git push origin develop
```

